Struggling with PCOD? Here’s an amazing Ayurvedic remedy shared by Dr. Kanchan Sharma that can help balance hormones and support your recovery naturally.

Herbal Remedy:

Mix the following and make a fine powder:
• 25g Ashok ki Chaal
• 25g Shatavari
• 50g Methi Dana

Take 1 spoon of this powder, boil it in 1 glass of water to make a kadha, and drink it daily.

Additional lifestyle tips:
• Avoid sugary, junk, and processed food
• Eat whole grains, fresh fruits, and vegetables
• Finish dinner by 7 PM
• Do 30 minutes of walk or yoga every day

This combination of herbs and lifestyle change can bring visible results in managing PCOD.

In this video, Dr. Varun Sharma explains how psoriasis works as an autoimmune disease and discusses its causes from both modern and Ayurvedic perspectives. According to modern science, factors such as genetics, an overactive immune system, stress/anxiety, and alcohol/smoking can trigger psoriasis. 

In Ayurveda, an imbalance in Vata and Kapha dosha along with the buildup of Aam dosha is seen as the root cause. Dr. Varun Sharma also highlights that many psoriasis patients may experience depression, anxiety, and even an infertility complex due to low self-esteem.

He then shares two effective home remedies for psoriasis: 

1. Aloe Vera & Coconut Oil Paste: 
 • Take fresh aloe vera and add 2 spoons of coconut oil. 
 • Apply this paste on areas with redness and itching. 

2. Herbal Paste: 
 • Mix white chandan powder, haldi (turmeric), and neem powder. 
 • Apply the paste directly to the affected areas.

Lifestyle changes are equally important: 
• Engage in daily exercise, yoga, and meditation. 
• Perform a body massage with castor oil. 
• Avoid chemical-based soaps; use neem water for bathing. 
• Consider neem giloy tablets for further support.

Dietary recommendations include: 

Foods to Avoid: 
1. Milk products 
2. Garlic 
3. Fish 
4. Incompatible food combinations (e.g., fish with milk, fruits with milk) 
5. Alcohol and smoking 
6. Urad dal 
7. Spicy food 

Foods to Include: 
• Red rice 
• Moong dal 
• Warm water 
• Light foods 
• Anti-inflammatory foods like giloy and neem

For personalized Ayurvedic guidance on managing psoriasis, contact us for a consultation.

Looking for a natural way to manage high cholesterol and high blood pressure ?

Dr. Varun Sharma shares an effective Ayurvedic remedy that helps control blood pressure, reduce cholesterol, and boost energy levels – all naturally!

💊 Remedy to control BP:

• 4 Gokshur seeds

Strain and drink it twice a day on an empty stomach for 1 month.

Clove Water Benefits Explained by Dr. Varun Sharma

Did you know that soaking just 4 cloves in water overnight can do wonders for your health?

Dr. Varun Sharma shares the Ayurvedic benefits of drinking clove water on an empty stomach:

* Helps relieve gas, acidity, and bloating
* Boosts digestion and appetite by increasing digestive fire
* Balances kapha dosha naturally
* Useful in managing stomach worms
* Purifies blood and may help reduce cholesterol levels

How to use:
Soak 4 cloves in a glass of water overnight. Strain and drink it first thing in the morning.

Natural, simple, and effective! Try it for a few weeks and feel the change.

Dr. Kanchan Sharma shares a magical Ayurvedic herb for women’s health and summer wellness 
Usheer / Vetiver Root, also known as Khas Khas ki Jad.

It is cooling in nature and offers multiple benefits:

1. Soak it overnight in water, strain and drink in the morning – it cools the body and is excellent in summers.
2. Use the same water to wash your face or body if you have acne or body acne.
3. Boil it at night and drink like tea – it reduces stress and improves sleep.
4. Mix its powder in buttermilk – great for digestion.
5. Women facing hot flashes during menopause – soak it with dhaniya seeds overnight and drink the water in the morning.

Try it consistently for a few weeks to feel the change.
